The '''Norwegian Actors' Equity Association''' ({{lang-no|Norsk Skuespillerforbund}}) is an association of Norwegian actors.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Norsk Skuespillerforbund |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |editor=Henriksen, Petter|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Norsk_Skuespillerforbund |language=Norwegian |accessdate=2 August 2009}}</ref> Its main purpose is to improve actors' working conditions and to protect the artistic, judicial and financial interests of actors in Norway.<ref>http://www.skuespillerforbund.no</ref> The association was established in 1898, after an initiative from actor Sigurd Asmundsen at a birthday party in 1897, followed by a preparatory meeting in April 1898, and a constituent meeting 27 October 1898.<ref name=nsf50>{{cite book |title=Norsk Skuespillerforbund gjennom 50 år, 1898–1948 |language=Norwegian |year=1948 |first=Egil |last=Hjorth-Jenssen |authorlink=Egil Hjorth-Jenssen |publisher=Gyldendal}}</ref> The first chairman was Sigvard Gundersen, with [[Johanne Dybwad]] as vice chairman, and [[Christian Sandal]] as first secretary.<ref name=nsf50 /> Important issues during the early years were contractual conditions, pensions, and regulation of foreign ensembles.<ref name=nsf50 /> The association's first Honorary member was actor and later theatrical director [[Bjørn Bjørnson]], nominated in May 1900.<ref name=nsf75>{{cite book |title=Så vidunderlig det er... Norsk Skuespillerforbund gjennom 75 år |language=Norwegian |year=1973 |first=Kåre |last=Fasting |page=237 |publisher=Gyldendal}}</ref>
The Association currently has 1250 members, of whom approximately 155 are permanently employed and 150 temporarily employed in institutional theatres.<ref>http://skuespillerforbund.no/english</ref> NAEA publishes [http://www.skuespillerkatalogen.no/ Skuespillerkatalogen] – the Actors' Catalogue. As the leading national casting resource, it is used by most Norwegian TV, Film, Radio and Theatre companies.<ref>http://skuespillerkatalogen.no</ref>
