{{Infobox Network | name = Radio Bulgaria (BNR) | logo = [[File:Bnr-radio-bulgaria.png|220px]] | country = {{BUL}} | network_type = [[Radio network]] | available = International | owner = [[Government of Bulgaria]] | key_people = Angel Nedyalkov (Director) | launch_date = March 30, 1930 | past_names = | website = http://www.bnr.bg/en |}}
'''Radio Bulgaria''' ([[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]]: Радио България, ''Radio Balgariya''; '''BNR''') is the official [[international broadcasting]] station of [[Bulgaria]].
== History == For almost seventy years the world service of the Bulgarian radio, formerly called Radio Sofia but now renamed Radio Bulgaria, has been presenting the country’s cultural and national identity to the world. It is a principal source of information from and about [[Bulgaria]] for millions of listeners outside its borders.{{cn|date=December 2017}}
== Current broadcasting ==
Radio Bulgaria ended its shortwave service on February 1, 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=As of February 1 Radio Bulgaria suspends shortwave broadcasts|url=http://bnr.bg/sites/en/Feedback/HiRadioBulgaria/Pages/1601%D0%918.aspx|accessdate=July 5, 2013|website=Radio Bulgaria|publisher=[[Bulgarian National Radio]]|date=January 16, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120830232342/http://bnr.bg/sites/en/Feedback/HiRadioBulgaria/Pages/1601%D0%918.aspx|archivedate=August 30, 2012|df=}}</ref>
